INSERT INTO questions (subject, topic, difficulty, question_text, choices, correct_answer, explanation, exam_type) VALUES
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','Which ancient civilization built the Great Pyramid of Giza?','[{"key":"A","text":"Greek"},{"key":"B","text":"Roman"},{"key":"C","text":"Mesopotamian"},{"key":"D","text":"Egyptian"}]','D','The Great Pyramid of Giza was built by the ancient Egyptians, specifically as the tomb of Pharaoh Khufu (Cheops), around 2560 BCE.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Magna Carta (1215) is significant because it:','[{"key":"A","text":"Gave the English king absolute power"},{"key":"B","text":"Established the principle that even the king is subject to the law"},{"key":"C","text":"Declared England''s independence from Rome"},{"key":"D","text":"Ended the Hundred Years'' War"}]','B','The Magna Carta (Great Charter), signed by King John of England, established that the king''s power was limited by law and laid the foundation for constitutional government.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The French Revolution began in the year:','[{"key":"A","text":"1776"},{"key":"B","text":"1789"},{"key":"C","text":"1801"},{"key":"D","text":"1815"}]','B','The French Revolution began in 1789 with the storming of the Bastille on July 14, 1789, which is now celebrated as Bastille Day.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Industrial Revolution began in:','[{"key":"A","text":"France"},{"key":"B","text":"Germany"},{"key":"C","text":"Great Britain"},{"key":"D","text":"United States"}]','C','The Industrial Revolution began in Great Britain in the late 18th century, driven by coal, steam power, and textile innovations, before spreading to other countries.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','World War I began in the year:','[{"key":"A","text":"1914"},{"key":"B","text":"1918"},{"key":"C","text":"1939"},{"key":"D","text":"1945"}]','A','World War I began on July 28, 1914, triggered by the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria-Hungary in Sarajevo.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Treaty of Versailles (1919) ended World War I and imposed harsh conditions on:','[{"key":"A","text":"France"},{"key":"B","text":"Great Britain"},{"key":"C","text":"Germany"},{"key":"D","text":"Austria-Hungary"}]','C','The Treaty of Versailles blamed Germany for WWI (War Guilt Clause), forced Germany to pay reparations, lose territories, and limit its military — conditions that contributed to WWII.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','World War II ended in 1945 with the surrender of:','[{"key":"A","text":"Germany and Japan"},{"key":"B","text":"Italy and Germany"},{"key":"C","text":"Japan and Italy"},{"key":"D","text":"Germany only"}]','A','WWII in Europe ended May 8, 1945 (V-E Day) with Germany''s surrender; WWII in the Pacific ended September 2, 1945 (V-J Day) with Japan''s surrender.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Cold War (1947-1991) was primarily a rivalry between:','[{"key":"A","text":"Britain and France"},{"key":"B","text":"USA and USSR"},{"key":"C","text":"China and Japan"},{"key":"D","text":"NATO and the United Nations"}]','B','The Cold War was a geopolitical tension between the United States (capitalism/democracy) and the Soviet Union (communism), characterized by proxy wars, nuclear arms race, and the Space Race.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The United Nations was founded in:','[{"key":"A","text":"1918"},{"key":"B","text":"1941"},{"key":"C","text":"1945"},{"key":"D","text":"1950"}]','C','The United Nations was established on October 24, 1945, after World War II to maintain international peace, security, and cooperation.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Which concept describes the idea that all people, regardless of birth, have the same fundamental rights?','[{"key":"A","text":"Sovereignty"},{"key":"B","text":"Natural law"},{"key":"C","text":"Human rights"},{"key":"D","text":"Social contract"}]','C','Human rights are rights inherent to all human beings, regardless of race, sex, nationality, or religion. The Universal Declaration of Human Rights (1948) codified these.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','The policy of "appeasement" before WWII refers to:','[{"key":"A","text":"The Allied invasion of Germany"},{"key":"B","text":"Britain and France conceding to Hitler''s demands to avoid war"},{"key":"C","text":"Germany''s policy of negotiating with the USSR"},{"key":"D","text":"Japan''s peace overtures to the USA"}]','B','The Munich Agreement (1938) saw Britain and France allow Hitler to annex Czechoslovakia''s Sudetenland, hoping to satisfy his ambitions and avoid war — a failed policy known as appeasement.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The Berlin Wall separated East and West Berlin from:','[{"key":"A","text":"1945-1955"},{"key":"B","text":"1961-1989"},{"key":"C","text":"1950-1975"},{"key":"D","text":"1945-1989"}]','B','The Berlin Wall was built by East Germany on August 13, 1961 and fell on November 9, 1989, symbolizing both the Cold War division of Europe and its end.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Supply and demand theory states that when the supply of a good decreases (demand unchanged), the price:','[{"key":"A","text":"Falls"},{"key":"B","text":"Rises"},{"key":"C","text":"Stays the same"},{"key":"D","text":"First rises then falls"}]','B','When supply decreases and demand stays the same, scarcity increases, pushing the equilibrium price upward.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','GDP stands for:','[{"key":"A","text":"Gross Domestic Product"},{"key":"B","text":"General Development Program"},{"key":"C","text":"Government Development Plan"},{"key":"D","text":"Gross Development Plan"}]','A','GDP (Gross Domestic Product) is the total monetary value of all goods and services produced within a country''s borders in a specific time period.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Inflation is defined as:','[{"key":"A","text":"A decrease in the general price level"},{"key":"B","text":"An increase in the general price level of goods and services over time"},{"key":"C","text":"A fall in unemployment rates"},{"key":"D","text":"An increase in the value of a country''s currency"}]','B','Inflation is a sustained increase in the general price level, reducing purchasing power. It is measured by the Consumer Price Index (CPI).','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','A monopoly is a market structure where:','[{"key":"A","text":"Many firms compete freely"},{"key":"B","text":"Two firms dominate the market"},{"key":"C","text":"One firm controls the entire market"},{"key":"D","text":"Prices are set by the government"}]','C','A monopoly is when a single seller or producer dominates a market, with no close substitutes, giving it price-making power.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The law of diminishing marginal returns states:','[{"key":"A","text":"Adding more workers always increases total output proportionally"},{"key":"B","text":"Beyond a certain point, adding more of one input (with others fixed) yields decreasing additional output"},{"key":"C","text":"Reducing workers always reduces output"},{"key":"D","text":"Technology always compensates for resource limits"}]','B','The law of diminishing returns: as more units of a variable input are added to a fixed input, the marginal (additional) output eventually decreases.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','In economics, "opportunity cost" refers to:','[{"key":"A","text":"The money paid for a product or service"},{"key":"B","text":"The cost of producing one more unit"},{"key":"C","text":"The value of the next best alternative forgone when a choice is made"},{"key":"D","text":"The total cost of production"}]','C','Opportunity cost is the value of the best alternative you give up when making a decision. It''s a fundamental concept explaining trade-offs.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Which of the following is a characteristic of a mixed economy?','[{"key":"A","text":"All resources are owned by the state"},{"key":"B","text":"All resources are privately owned with no government intervention"},{"key":"C","text":"Both private enterprise and government play roles in the economy"},{"key":"D","text":"Prices are determined solely by tradition"}]','C','A mixed economy combines elements of free market capitalism (private ownership, market prices) and government intervention (regulations, public services, social safety nets).','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The Renaissance (14th-17th centuries) was a cultural movement that began in:','[{"key":"A","text":"France"},{"key":"B","text":"Germany"},{"key":"C","text":"England"},{"key":"D","text":"Italy"}]','D','The Renaissance (rebirth) began in Italy in the 14th century, marked by renewed interest in classical Greek and Roman knowledge, arts, and science.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Protestant Reformation was initiated by:','[{"key":"A","text":"Henry VIII of England"},{"key":"B","text":"Martin Luther in Germany"},{"key":"C","text":"John Calvin in Switzerland"},{"key":"D","text":"Pope Leo X"}]','B','Martin Luther began the Protestant Reformation in 1517 by posting his 95 Theses criticizing the Catholic Church''s practice of selling indulgences.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','The Age of Exploration (15th-17th centuries) was primarily driven by:','[{"key":"A","text":"Scientific curiosity alone"},{"key":"B","text":"The desire to spread Islam globally"},{"key":"C","text":"Economic motives (trade routes, resources) and technological advances in navigation"},{"key":"D","text":"Population pressure in Europe"}]','C','European exploration was driven by the desire for direct trade routes to Asia (spices, silk), new resources, religious conversion goals, and advances in navigation (compass, caravel ships).','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The American Declaration of Independence was adopted in:','[{"key":"A","text":"1776"},{"key":"B","text":"1783"},{"key":"C","text":"1789"},{"key":"D","text":"1787"}]','A','The American Declaration of Independence was adopted on July 4, 1776, declaring independence from British rule. This date is celebrated as Independence Day in the USA.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Colonialism refers to:','[{"key":"A","text":"The peaceful cultural exchange between nations"},{"key":"B","text":"The policy of a stronger nation controlling and exploiting a weaker one"},{"key":"C","text":"International trade agreements between equal nations"},{"key":"D","text":"The internal politics of a nation"}]','B','Colonialism is the practice by which a powerful nation acquires and maintains territories (colonies), exploiting their resources and peoples for the colonizer''s benefit.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The concept of "separation of powers" in government means:','[{"key":"A","text":"Different nations governing different regions"},{"key":"B","text":"Distributing governmental power among executive, legislative, and judicial branches"},{"key":"C","text":"Separating civilians from the military"},{"key":"D","text":"Dividing national budget among government departments"}]','B','Separation of powers (Montesquieu) divides government into three branches — executive, legislative, judicial — each with distinct powers to prevent concentration of authority.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','The Bolshevik Revolution of 1917 in Russia established:','[{"key":"A","text":"A constitutional monarchy"},{"key":"B","text":"A democratic republic"},{"key":"C","text":"A communist state led by the Bolshevik Party"},{"key":"D","text":"A military dictatorship"}]','C','The October Revolution (1917) led by Vladimir Lenin and the Bolsheviks overthrew the Provisional Government, establishing the world''s first communist state — the Soviet Union.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The Holocaust during World War II refers to:','[{"key":"A","text":"The German invasion of Poland"},{"key":"B","text":"The systematic genocide of 6 million Jews by Nazi Germany"},{"key":"C","text":"The bombing of Hiroshima and Nagasaki"},{"key":"D","text":"The Battle of Stalingrad"}]','B','The Holocaust was the state-sponsored, systematic persecution and genocide of approximately 6 million Jews (and millions of others) by Nazi Germany under Adolf Hitler.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) was founded in:','[{"key":"A","text":"1945"},{"key":"B","text":"1967"},{"key":"C","text":"1975"},{"key":"D","text":"1991"}]','B','ASEAN was founded on August 8, 1967 in Bangkok, Thailand by 5 original members: Philippines, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, and Thailand.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','Capitalism is an economic system characterized by:','[{"key":"A","text":"State ownership of all means of production"},{"key":"B","text":"Private ownership of means of production and free market competition"},{"key":"C","text":"Government central planning of the economy"},{"key":"D","text":"Equal distribution of all resources"}]','B','Capitalism is based on private ownership of property and means of production, free market competition, and the profit motive.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Fiscal policy refers to the government''s use of:','[{"key":"A","text":"Interest rates and money supply to manage the economy"},{"key":"B","text":"Taxation and government spending to influence the economy"},{"key":"C","text":"Trade tariffs to protect local industries"},{"key":"D","text":"Currency exchange rates"}]','B','Fiscal policy uses government spending and taxation to influence macroeconomic conditions like employment, inflation, and economic growth.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','The concept of "comparative advantage" in international trade means:','[{"key":"A","text":"A country should produce everything it needs domestically"},{"key":"B","text":"Countries should specialize in producing goods for which they have the lowest opportunity cost"},{"key":"C","text":"Larger countries always have an advantage in trade"},{"key":"D","text":"Countries should avoid trade deficits at all costs"}]','B','Comparative advantage (Ricardo) holds that nations benefit from specializing in goods they produce most efficiently (lowest opportunity cost) and trading for the rest.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Great Depression of the 1930s began with:','[{"key":"A","text":"The bombing of Pearl Harbor"},{"key":"B","text":"The Wall Street Crash of 1929"},{"key":"C","text":"The Treaty of Versailles"},{"key":"D","text":"The Russian Revolution"}]','B','The Great Depression was triggered by the stock market crash of October 1929 ("Black Tuesday"), leading to massive unemployment and economic collapse worldwide.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','Urbanization refers to:','[{"key":"A","text":"The decrease in city populations"},{"key":"B","text":"The movement of people from rural to urban areas"},{"key":"C","text":"Government planning of cities"},{"key":"D","text":"Industrialization of rural farms"}]','B','Urbanization is the process by which rural populations move to cities and towns, often driven by economic opportunities and industrialization.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Democracy originated in:','[{"key":"A","text":"Ancient Rome"},{"key":"B","text":"Ancient Egypt"},{"key":"C","text":"Ancient Greece (Athens)"},{"key":"D","text":"Ancient China"}]','C','Democracy (demos = people, kratos = rule) originated in ancient Athens, Greece around the 5th century BCE under leaders like Cleisthenes and Pericles.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','Monetary policy is controlled by the:','[{"key":"A","text":"Department of Finance"},{"key":"B","text":"President of the Philippines"},{"key":"C","text":"Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas (BSP)"},{"key":"D","text":"House of Representatives"}]','C','In the Philippines, monetary policy (money supply, interest rates, inflation) is managed by the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas (BSP), the central bank.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The Silk Road was an ancient trade route connecting:','[{"key":"A","text":"Africa and South America"},{"key":"B","text":"China and the Mediterranean/Europe"},{"key":"C","text":"India and Southeast Asia"},{"key":"D","text":"Arabia and East Africa"}]','B','The Silk Road was a network of ancient trade routes connecting China and East Asia with Central Asia, South Asia, the Middle East, and Europe.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Supply-side economics advocates:','[{"key":"A","text":"Increasing government spending to stimulate demand"},{"key":"B","text":"Reducing taxes and regulations to stimulate production and economic growth"},{"key":"C","text":"Raising minimum wage to boost consumer spending"},{"key":"D","text":"Nationalizing key industries"}]','B','Supply-side economics (Reaganomics/trickle-down economics) holds that cutting taxes on businesses and the wealthy stimulates investment, production, and economic growth.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','Which philosopher''s social contract theory most directly influenced the American Declaration of Independence?','[{"key":"A","text":"Thomas Hobbes"},{"key":"B","text":"John Locke"},{"key":"C","text":"Jean-Jacques Rousseau"},{"key":"D","text":"Montesquieu"}]','B','John Locke''s ideas (natural rights: life, liberty, and property; government by consent; right to revolt) directly influenced Jefferson''s writing of the Declaration of Independence.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','The Non-Aligned Movement during the Cold War consisted of nations that:','[{"key":"A","text":"Supported the USA against the USSR"},{"key":"B","text":"Supported the USSR against the USA"},{"key":"C","text":"Sought to remain neutral and independent from both superpowers"},{"key":"D","text":"Formed a third military alliance"}]','C','The Non-Aligned Movement (founded 1961) united developing nations seeking independence from both US and Soviet influence during the Cold War.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','What does "per capita income" mean?','[{"key":"A","text":"Total income of a country"},{"key":"B","text":"Average income per person"},{"key":"C","text":"Income of the richest 10% of the population"},{"key":"D","text":"Government revenue per year"}]','B','Per capita income = total national income ÷ total population. It measures the average economic well-being of the citizens.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','What event marked the beginning of the nuclear age?','[{"key":"A","text":"The development of the atomic bomb in the Manhattan Project (1945)"},{"key":"B","text":"The bombing of London during WWII"},{"key":"C","text":"The founding of the United Nations (1945)"},{"key":"D","text":"The Cold War arms race (1950s)"}]','A','The Manhattan Project (1942-1945) developed the first nuclear weapons. The bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki in August 1945 marked the first and only wartime use of nuclear weapons.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','hard','"Glasnost" and "Perestroika" were reforms introduced by Soviet leader _____ that contributed to the collapse of the USSR.','[{"key":"A","text":"Joseph Stalin"},{"key":"B","text":"Mikhail Gorbachev"},{"key":"C","text":"Boris Yeltsin"},{"key":"D","text":"Nikita Khrushchev"}]','B','Mikhail Gorbachev (1985-1991) introduced glasnost (openness/transparency) and perestroika (restructuring) to reform the Soviet system, but these reforms accelerated its collapse.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','easy','The policy of racial segregation in South Africa was called:','[{"key":"A","text":"Imperialism"},{"key":"B","text":"Colonialism"},{"key":"C","text":"Apartheid"},{"key":"D","text":"Nationalism"}]','C','Apartheid (Afrikaans for "separateness") was South Africa''s system of institutionalized racial segregation from 1948-1994, ended largely through the efforts of Nelson Mandela.','secondary'),
('General Education','Social Studies','medium','Which of the following best defines "globalization"?','[{"key":"A","text":"The spread of democratic governance worldwide"},{"key":"B","text":"The increasing integration and interdependence of economies, cultures, and peoples worldwide"},{"key":"C","text":"Military cooperation among the world''s nations"},{"key":"D","text":"The process of industrialization in developing nations"}]','B','Globalization refers to the process by which the world''s markets, cultures, and political systems become increasingly interconnected through trade, technology, and communication.','secondary');
